(43, 'Experimental Genome Science', 'Each of our cells contains nearly identical copies of our genome, which provides instructions that allow us to develop and function. This course serves as an introduction to the main laboratory and theoretical aspects of genomics and is divided into themes: genomes, genetics, functional genomics, systems biology, single cell approaches, proteomics, and applications.', 'Each of our cells contains nearly identical copies of our genome, which provides instructions that allow us to develop and function. This course serves as an introduction to the main laboratory and theoretical aspects of genomics and is divided into themes: genomes, genetics, functional genomics, systems biology, single cell approaches, proteomics, and applications.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/genomescience', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WTvntDF4XL8', '2012-10-15', 14, 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/coursera/topics/genomescience/large-icon.png', 'Biology & Life Sciences', 'coursera'),
(44, 'Basic Behavioral Neurology', 'This course will survey fundamental principles of cognitive and behavioral neurology. The emphasis of the course will be on the neural mechanisms underlying aspects of cognition and on diseases that affect intellect and behavior. No prior background in neurology, medicine, or neuroscience is required.', 'This course will survey fundamental principles of cognitive and behavioral neurology. The emphasis of the course will be on the neural mechanisms underlying aspects of cognition and on diseases that affect intellect and behavior. No prior background in neurology, medicine, or neuroscience is required.', 'https://www.coursera.org/course/neurobehavior', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ceFOoPrw93c', '0000-00-00', 4, 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/coursera/topics/neurobehavior/large-icon.png', 'Medicine', 'coursera'),
